<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1323,1073,1779]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[437,578,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">V. m a l a y a n a</emphasis>
differs from 
<emphasis box="[738,852,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">V. ro b u s t a</emphasis>
in having less anteriorly produced connective and style beyond anterior margin of pygophore, slender, elongate ventral processes of aedeagus which are distally serrated. Aedeagus is separated from ventral process and apically flared. Anal segments are more slender and elongate in 
<taxonomicName box="[1049,1165,1713,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vartalapa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malayana">
<emphasis box="[1049,1165,1713,1738]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">malayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to those in 
<taxonomicName box="[364,452,1753,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Vartalapa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[364,452,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
